<ChannelTradeLayout
  title="AI Website Chat for UK HVAC Contractors | Rapid Receptionist"
  description={`AI website chat for UK HVAC contractors. Engages homeowners researching heat pumps and facilities managers comparing VRF systems. Included at £${pricing.tiers.core.price}/month.`}
  canonicalUrl="/hvac-contractors/ai-website-chat/"
  channelName="AI Website Chat"
  tradeName="HVAC Contractor"
  tradeNamePlural="HVAC Contractors"
  tradeSlug="hvac-contractors"
  headline="AI Website Chat for UK HVAC Contractor Companies"
  accentWord="HVAC"
  subhead="A homeowner finds your website at 10pm on a September Tuesday. She lives in a 1930s semi-detached house in Summertown with solid brick walls, single-glazed sash windows being replaced next month with double-glazed timber frames, and an ageing oil boiler in the garage. Her oil bill last winter was £2,800. She has read about air source heat pumps and the £7,500 BUS grant but is confused about whether her house is suitable — the solid walls worry her, the radiators are original cast iron, and she has heard heat pumps need underfloor heating. She types: 'Evening — we have a 1930s semi with solid brick walls, currently on oil heating. Oil bill was £2,800 last year. Thinking about an air source heat pump but worried our house is too old. We are getting new double-glazed windows next month. Radiators are old cast iron — do they need replacing? Do we qualify for the £7,500 grant? How much would a heat pump cost installed after the grant? The oil tank is in the back garden — we would love to get rid of it. We are in Summertown, four bedrooms, one bathroom.' Without chat, she bookmarks and calls during the week. With AI Website Chat, the AI explains that solid-wall properties can be suitable for heat pumps especially after glazing upgrades and that cast iron radiators often have sufficient surface area for low-temperature operation, then asks about the cavity status and loft insulation. She confirms 100mm loft insulation and no cavity. Wednesday you call: Summertown 1930s 4-bed semi, solid brick, cast iron radiators, oil boiler, £2,800 oil bill, new DG windows next month, BUS grant query, 100mm loft insulation, no cavity, oil tank removal."
  scenario="It is midnight on a Friday. A property developer types: 'Hi — we are building a development of twenty-four zero-carbon homes in Bicester. Need HVAC package: Mitsubishi Ecodan monobloc ASHPs for each property, MVHR by Zehnder ComfoAir Q450, underfloor heating throughout, no radiators, smart controls via Mitsubishi MELCloud app. Part L 2025 compliance mandatory. Also need three show homes completed two months ahead of the main programme for marketing. Can you deliver MCS-certified ASHP installations at this scale, and do you handle the BUS grant applications on behalf of the homebuyers? Programme kicks off in fourteen weeks.' Without chat, he emails Monday. With AI Website Chat, the AI confirms your MCS certification and multi-unit capability, asks about the ground conditions for pipework routing and the DNO supply capacity, and captures: Bicester 24 zero-carbon homes, Mitsubishi Ecodan monobloc, Zehnder ComfoAir Q450 MVHR, UFH throughout, MELCloud controls, Part L 2025, 3 show homes early, BUS grant applications, MCS certified, 14 weeks."
  benefits={benefits}
  faqs={faqs}
  channelPageUrl="/construction-trades/ai-website-chat/"
  tradePageUrl="/hvac-contractors/ai-receptionist/"
  ctaHeadline="Win the Summertown Heat Pump Conversion While She Calculates Oil Savings"
  ctaSubhead={`A homeowner with £2,800 oil bills, new windows arriving next month, and cast iron radiators perfect for low-temperature heating needs MCS guidance at 10pm. Chat captures the BUS grant query. Included at £${pricing.tiers.core.price}/month.`}
